Preconditions:
- The input array `arr` is not null.
- The length of the input array `arr` is even.
- The length of the input array `arr` is at least 2.
- Each element in the input array `arr` is a positive integer.
- Each element in the input array `arr` is less than or equal to 10^5.

Postconditions:
- The output is an integer representing the minimum size of the set.
- The output is greater than or equal to 1.
- The output is less than or equal to half the length of the input array `arr`.
- After removing the chosen set of integers from the input array `arr`, at least half of the integers in the array are removed.